Into to CSS: what is CSS?
CSS = Cascading Style Sheets
    - A Cascade is like a waterfall; water at one level drops down into
another and that into another one etc.
    - A Style Sheet is a language that allows us to specify how things should look on our website. Similar to how html is a Markup Language (ht'ML'), c'SS' is a 'Style Sheet' Language. Many different types of style sheet languages, CSS is just one of them.

3 Ways to Add CSS to a website:
1. Inline: <tag style="css">
    i.e. <html style="background:blue"></html> , where property = background, value = blue
    Useful for adding a css style to a SINGLE ELEMENT on your html page

2. Internal: <style>css</style>
    i.e. <html>
            <head>
                <style>
                    html { # This html is called a selector and the css goes in between curly braces
                        background: red;
                    }
                </style>
            </head>
         </html>
    Useful if you're applying it in only 1 html document i.e. SINGLE WEBPAGE

3. External: <link href="style.css"/>
    i.e. index.html file:
    <html>
        <head>
            <link
            rel="stylesheet" # rel = relationship; what is the role of this thing that we're linking to
            href="./styles.css" # href = location; where in the directory is it located
            />
        </head>
    </html>
    styles.css file:
    html {
        background:green;
    }
    Useful for a SINGLE WEBSITE